tourBios.carHigh:
2013: Made the cut in eight of 19 starts during his rookie Web.com Tour season. Had five top-25 finishes and one top-10...Missed the cut in eight of his first 10 starts...Lone top-10 finish (T9) came at The Rex Hospital Open in June when he shot 65-74-66-67 to jump from 127th in earnings to 84th...Posted four finishes of T19 or better in his last nine starts...Got as high as 79th on the earnings' chart after the Price Cutter Charity Championship. 

2012: Monday-qualifed into the PGA TOUR's John Deere Classic, where he made his first cut in his second career TOUR start. Finished T45. Had never played a Web.com Tour event prior to 2013...Finished fourth on the Hooters Tour money list after nine top-20 finishes in 15 starts. 2011: Won his first professional event, at the Michigan Open. 2009: Missed the cut at the PGA TOUR's Buick Open.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Made the all-state super team in golf his last three years of high school...All conference in basketball his senior year at Traverse City Central in Michigan...Four-year letterwinner at Michigan State University...Made first-team All Big Ten Conference as a junior...Won the Fighting Irish Classic in college...Finished college career ranked on the MSU career scoring list.
tourBios.personal: Favorite golf memory is breaking 70 for the first time...Twitter account is @RH_Golfer...Follows all Detroit professional sports teams...Would like to switch places with the President of the United States.

tourBios.carHigh: Won his first professional event at the 2011 Michigan Open...Played on PGA TOUR Canada in 2010 and the Hooters Tour in 2011 and 2012.
